    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const jobs = $input.first().json.jobs;\n\nconst prompt = `\nYou are an expert technical recruiter.\n\nYou will receive a JSON array called \"jobs\".\n\nYour task is to FILTER the jobs.\n\n==============================\nKEEP THE JOB IF:\n==============================\n\n1. The title contains any of these:\n\n- Data Analyst\n- Business Analyst\n- Reporting Analyst\n- Operations Analyst\n- Process Analyst\n- MIS Analyst\n- Risk Analyst\n- Financial Analyst\n- BI Analyst\n- Associate Analyst\n- Junior Analyst\n\nAND\n\n2. The description DOES NOT clearly require more than 2 years experience.\n\n==============================\nREJECT IMMEDIATELY IF:\n==============================\n\nThe title OR description contains ANY of:\n\n- Senior\n- Lead\n- Principal\n- Manager\n- Director\n- Architect\n- Consultant\n- Staff Engineer\n\nOR\n\n- 3 years\n- 3+ years\n- 4 years\n- 4+ years\n- 5 years\n- 5+ years\n- 6+ years\n- 7+ years\n- 8+ years\n- 9+ years\n- 10+ years\n\n==============================\nIMPORTANT\n==============================\n\nIf the experience is NOT mentioned,\n\nDO NOT reject it.\n\nInstead:\n\nIf it looks like an entry-level analyst role,\nKEEP it.\n\nOnly reject jobs that clearly require experienced candidates.\n\n==============================\nOUTPUT\n==============================\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON.\n\nNo markdown.\n\nNo explanation.\n\nReturn exactly:\n\n{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"company\": \"\",\n      \"title\": \"\",\n      \"location\": \"\",\n      \"apply_link\": \"\",\n      \"reason\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nJobs:\n\n${JSON.stringify(jobs)}\n`;\n\nreturn [\n  {\n    json: {\n      contents: [\n        {\n          parts: [\n            {\n              text: prompt\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -1088,
        -160
      ],
      "name": "Code in JavaScript1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const response = $input.first().json;\n\nconst text = response.candidates[0].content.parts[0].text;\n\n// Remove markdown if Gemini ever adds it\nconst cleaned = text\n  .replace(/```json/g, \"\")\n  .replace(/```/g, \"\")\n  .trim();\n\n// Convert JSON string to object\nconst parsed = JSON.parse(cleaned);\n\nreturn [\n  {\n    json: parsed\n  }\n];"
      },
